The White House announced that it will host its first ever Twitter town hall on July 6th. Twitter users can submit questions using the hashtag #AskObama. Press Secretary Jay Carney answered questions about the President's involvement in negotiations with Congress over the debt ceiling, his decision to go to fundraisers in Philadelphia, and the August 2nd deadline for raising the debt ceiling. Carney also discussed the President's position on tax subsidies, defense spending cuts, and the Greek debt crisis. He criticized the maximalist position of some Republicans and emphasized the need for a balanced and fair deficit reduction deal. Carney also commented on the President's tough tone towards Congress and his commitment to comprehensive immigration reform.